Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

         "VAADMIN"."MVW_OUTLETWISE_SIM_BURN" Select KK.ACTIVEOUTLETUID
         OUTLETUID,KK.ACT_MONTH TRAN_DATE,KK.ACT_COUNT SIM_VALUE
         FROM (
         SELECT S.ACTIVEOUTLETUID,COUNT(S.PUID)
         ACT_COUNT,TRUNC(S.ACTIVATIONDATE,'MM') ACT_MONTH
         FROM SIM S
         WHERE S.ACTIVATIONDATE >= TRUNC(SYSDATE,'MON')
         AND S.ACTIVATIONDATE <= TRUNC(SYSDATE,'DDD')
         GROUP BY S.ACTIVEOUTLETUID, TRUNC(S.ACTIVATIONDATE,'MM')
         UNION ALL
         SELECT S.ACTIVEOUTLETUID,COUNT(S.PUID)
         ACT_COUNT,TRUNC(S.ACTIVATIONDATE,'MM') ACT_MONTH
         FROM SIM S
         WHERE S.ACTIVATIONDATE >= TRUNC(ADD_MONTHS(SYSDATE,-1),'MON')
         AND S.ACTIVATIONDATE <= TRUNC(ADD_MONTHS(SYSDATE,-1),'DDD')
         GROUP BY S.ACTIVEOUTLETUID, TRUNC(S.ACTIVATIONDATE,'MM')
         )KK

   Estimated benefit is .09 active sessions, 2.17% of total activity.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------

      consider slowing down RMAN activity, or scheduling RMAN jobs when user
      activity is lower.


Finding 6: Undersized instance memory
Impact is .07 active sessions, 1.85% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------
The Oracle instance memory (SGA and PGA) was inadequately sized, causing
additional I/O and CPU usage.
The value of parameter "memory_target" was "32768 M" during the analysis
period.

   Recommendation 1: Database Configuration
   Estimated benefit is .07 active sessions, 1.85% of total activity.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Increase memory allocated to the instance by setting the parameter
      "memory_target" to 57344 M.

   Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
   ---------------------------------
      Wait class "User I/O" was consuming significant database time.
      Impact is 1.95 active sessions, 48.19% of total activity.
